@startuml uc-11
autonumber
skinparam maxMessageSize 150
skinparam ParticipantPadding 20
skinparam BoxPadding 10

actor "Faculty Board Member" as Board

box "Presentation Layer" #LightCyan
participant "ui : FacultyBoardUI" as UI
end box

box "Business Logic Layer" #LightYellow
participant "controller : FacultyBoardController" as Controller
end box

box "Data Access Layer" #LightGreen
participant "appRecord : TransferApplication" as AppDB
participant "evalRecord : EvaluationReport" as EvalDB
participant "decisionRecord : BoardDecision" as DecisionDB
end box

== Application Review ==
Board -> UI: Select applicant for final board review
activate UI

UI -> Controller: fetchApplicationDetails(applicationId)
activate Controller

Controller -> AppDB: Retrieve TransferApplication
activate AppDB
AppDB --> Controller: Application data
deactivate AppDB

Controller -> EvalDB: Retrieve EvaluationReport & Intibak details
activate EvalDB
EvalDB --> Controller: Evaluation and Intibak data
deactivate EvalDB



Controller --> UI: Consolidated application data
UI --> Board: displayConsolidatedReport()
deactivate Controller

== Decision Making ==
alt Application Approved (Normal Flow)
    Board -> UI: Click "Approve"
    UI -> Controller: recordFinalDecision(applicationId, "Approved", null)
    activate Controller
    
else Application Rejected (Alternative Flow)
    Board -> UI: Click "Reject"
    UI --> Board: showRejectionCodeDropdown()
    Board -> UI: Select rejection code (e.g., "Insufficient Equivalency") 
    Board -> UI: Enter additional comments and confirm
    UI -> Controller: recordFinalDecision(applicationId, "Rejected", rejectionCode)
end

== Recording the Decision ==
Controller -> DecisionDB: Create BoardDecision(decisionType, rejectionCode, timestamp)
activate DecisionDB
DecisionDB --> Controller: BoardDecision saved
deactivate DecisionDB

Controller -> AppDB: Update finalDecision status & link BoardDecision
activate AppDB
AppDB --> Controller: Status updated
deactivate AppDB

Controller --> UI: Decision successfully recorded
deactivate Controller

UI --> Board: Display confirmation message & return to application list
deactivate UI

@enduml